tool.name: GDVSpectra_CVA

param.name: in_raw_nc_path
param.dialogReference:
The input raw satellite data NetCDF file generated from the COG Fetch module. Requires x, y, time and satellite band variables.

Note: if you do not have a satellite NetCDF, run the COG Fetch tool first.

param.name: in_mask_nc_path
param.displayname: Input GDV Threshold mask NetCDF file
param.dialogReference: A GDV Likelihood Threshold NetCDF generated by the GDV Threshold. The Threshold areas act as a mask to reduce analysis down to high likelihood vegetation areas. Requires x, y, time and a Likelihood variable.

param.name: out_nc_path
param.dialogReference: The folder location and filename of the output NetCDF file containing CVA map data.

param.name: in_base_start_year
param.dialogReference:
The start date of the baseline period. All satellite data prior to this date will be excluded. If more than one year provided for start and end baseline dates, a median of all images will be used.

All comparison images will be compared to this baseline.

The default value is the first date detected in the input NetCDF.

param.name: in_base_end_year
param.dialogReference:
The end date of the baseline period. All satellite data after this date will be excluded. If more than one year provided for start and end baseline dates, a median of all images will be used.

All comparison images will be compared to this baseline.

The default value is the first date detected in the input NetCDF.

param.name: in_comp_start_year
param.dialogReference:
The start date of the comparison period. All satellite data prior to this date will be excluded.

Each year within the comparison start and end period will be compared to the same baseline separately.

The default value is the first date detected in the input NetCDF.

param.name: in_comp_end_year
param.dialogReference:
The end date of the comparison period. All satellite data prior to this date will be excluded.

Each year within the comparison start and end period will be compared to the same baseline separately.

The default value is the first date detected in the input NetCDF.

param.name: in_analysis_months
param.dialogReference:
The month(s) to compare every year. If more than one month is selected, a median of these months is used.

Select all months to compare within whole years, or several months to compare within seasons.

param.name: in_tmf
param.dialogReference:
The magnitude threshold factor (also known as threshold median factor). Used to calculate a threshold magnitude for which pixels are considered stable, i.e. no change.

The default value is 2 times the median non-zero magnitude.

param.name: in_stand_qupper
param.dialogReference:
The upper n percentile of the vegetation and moisture index values. Used during invariant target standardisation and rescaling. The percentile is used as the maximum is prone to severe outliers.

The default value is recommended as it typically produces optimal results.

param.name: in_stand_qlower
param.dialogReference:
The lower n percentile of the vegetation and moisture index values. Used during invariant target standardisation and rescaling. The percentile is used as the minimum is prone to severe outliers.

The default value is recommended as it typically produces optimal results.

param.name: in_fmask_flags
param.expression: NoData | Valid | Cloud | Shadow | Snow | Water
param.dialogReference:
Classes captured within the OA measurement band provided for each satellite image via the DEA Fmask algorithm.

Only the selected pixel classes will be returned, whilst all others will be set to NoData (i.e., masked out).

param.name: in_max_cloud
param.dialogReference:
The maximum percentage of cloud cover existing per satellite image before it is discarded from analysis.

A value of 0 will return all satellite data with no cloud cover. A value of 10 will discard all satellite data with 11% or more cloud presence. A value of 100 will return all images regardless.

param.name: in_interpolate
param.dialogReference:
Whether to interpolate erroneous pixels that are masked out via the Mask band.

If checked, linear interpolation is applied along the time dimension of the input NetCDF, and missing pixels are filled.

param.name: in_add_result_to_map
param.dialogReference: Whether to visualise the results to the currently active map once modelling is complete or not.

tool.summary:
Performs a Change Vector Analysis (CVA) the Tasselled Cap index derived from raw satellite NetCDF data. CVA calculates angle and magnitude of change vectors between two satellite images (i.e., the base and comparison image), and from these angles certain types of change can be isolated (e.g., angles between 90-180 degrees indicate bare soil increase or vegetation decline). Additionally, magnitude can be used to highlight the amount of change that occurred.

This method takes a NetCDF of raw satellite imagery, calculates a greenness and brightness band from the Tasselled Cap index for every image in the NetCDF, then based on the user-defined base and comparison date ranges, creates a libray of CVA angle and magnitude maps.

See citation: Chen, J., Gong, P., He, C., Pu, R. and Shi, P., 2003. Land-use/land-cover change detection using improved change-vector analysis. Photogrammetric Engineering & Remote Sensing, 69(4), pp.369-379.
